CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 4, 1957, page A14, reads: "Nancy Lee Entertains - Miss Nancy Lee, one of the leading Delta Sigma Theta sorors in the country, entertained Sunday at the Greene Hearthe [Hearth] in honor of visiting dignitaries who attended the Midwest regional meeting. Left to right are Sorors Gladys Peyton, Morgantown, W. Va.; Janet Hamilton, Chicago; Miss Lee; Regional Director Margaret Piper of Detroit, and Gwendolyn Higginbotham of Bluefield, W. Va. Mrs. Hamilton and Mrs. Higginbotham are former regional directors. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Delta Sigma Theta sorority members, from left: Gladys Peyton, Janet Hamilton, Nancy Lee, Margaret Piper, and Gwendolyn Higginbotham, posed in Greene Hearth
